Hello Watanabe-san!

As an experienced agricultural extension officer specializing in paddy rice, I'm here to help you with your crop management. 

First, let's check on the growth stage of your rice plants. How many plants do you have currently?
User {{#if plant_count}}
{{#each plant as |p|}}
{{>plant_data @p.id}}
{{else}}
{{>plant_count}}
{{/each}}
{{/if}}

Great, that's good to know! Now, let's take a look at the soil conditions. How is your soil currently holding up?
User {{#if soil_moisture}}
{{>plant_data @soil_moisture.id}}
{{else}}
{{>soil_moisture_info @soil_moisture.id}}
{{/if}}

<strong>Air temperature:</strong> The temperature can affect the rice's growth and ripening process. What is the current temperature at your location?
User {{#if air_temperature}}
{{>air_temperature @air_temperature.id}}
{{else}}
{{>air_temperature_info @air_temperature.id}}
{{/if}}

The next thing we'll check is how your crops are faring against pests and diseases. Do you have any concerns or issues you'd like to address regarding pests or diseases?
User {{#if plant_pests}}
{{>plant_pests @plant_pests.id}}
{{else}}
{{>plant_pests_info @plant_pests.id}}
{{/if}}

<strong>Soil nutrients:</strong> Keeping a good balance of nutrient content in your soil is essential for crop growth. How are you currently providing the necessary nutrients to your plants?
User {{#if soil_nutrients}}
{{>soil_nutrients @soil_nutrients.id}}
{{else}}
{{>soil_nutrients_info @soil_nutrients.id}}
{{/if}}

Last but not least, we'll check in on the growth progress of your crops. Do you have any specific questions regarding crop growth and development?
User {{#if crop_data}}
{{>crop_data @crop_data.id}}
{{else}}
{{>crop_data_info @crop_data.id}}
{{/if}}


